  "text": "Accurately 1 g mayonnaise was weighed into a 50 ml volumetric flask and 1 g sea sand was added to complete saponification. Then, 20 ml freshly prepared 1.0 M methanolic potassium hydroxide solution and 10 ml isopropanol were added. In the next step, this solution was heated in a water batch at 60°C under a reflux condenser for 30 min while stirring with a magnetic stirrer. After cooling the turbid solution, 50 ml isopropanol was added and the fluid was filtered through Watmann no. 5 A filter paper. The clear sample solution was retained for the assay [CITATION_1] . Enzymatic measurement was used to determine the cholesterol content of different solutions by using Pars Azmoon diagnostic kits.",
